What does it take to give a supercar its unique sound? As you might expect, it's more than just the engine.

Everything has to be considered when engineering a cars' audio character. And for the McLaren Artura, we pushed ourselves to the limit of what was possible with technology today.

The result is a car that has a hugely diverse sound, capable of being scintillating at the top of the rev range, but comfortable while cruising.

How did we do it? Laurence Reucroft, Senior Project Engineer explains...

node.text:
Endurance racing isn't really like anything else.

A race car has to go through an almost unthinkable set of stats. At #SPA24H, that means more than 500 laps of a 7km circuit. Race distances can be over 3500km, with most laps averaging 140mph plus.

To pull it off, a car needs an incredible team. Everyone from technicians to team principles, to the drivers themselves, work together to go as fast as they possibly can.

For @jota_sport, night follows day. With 5hrs 25mins to go and in P8, everyone digs deep to bring the car home.

#Racing #Spa24h #Motorsport #McLaren

It's go time at #SPA24H 

@jota_sport started in P6 in the #McLaren720S GT3, with @ben_barnicoat at the wheel.

Spa circuit is one of the most challenging tracks in the world, with typically ever changing conditions. For the drivers putting a car around it for 24 hours, it's a huge effort.

So far, we've had a dry start moving into torrential rain. But for Ben Barnicoat it proved beneficial, as a mega drive in the wet sees Jota currently in P3, with @rob.bell79 now behind the wheel.

Stay tuned. More to come.

It's time for Superpole at #Spa24h.

We're here with @jota_sport who are headed out with driver @ben_barnicoat at the wheel. 

What's Superpole? The fastest 20 cars from qualifying have 2 laps each to go as fast as they can to determine the final grid order for the race tomorrow.

What next? A gruelling 24 hours at the iconic Spa circuit where the 720S GT3 will tackle one of the greatest corners in motorsport, Eau Rouge, over 500 times.

node.text:
Like every LT, the new Spider is designed to excel on track, however, the extra dimension of theatre and drama offered by the convertible roof also makes it an even more immersive and compelling car to drive on the road.​

#McLaren765LT #McLaren765LTSpider #Supercar #McLaren

node.text:
The fastest, lightest LT Spider yet pushes the limits of technology and design with its one-piece carbon fibre Retractable Hard Top (RHT). Powered by eight e-motors, the system is almost silent in operation. It also opens in just 11 seconds at speeds of up to 50km/h.

#McLaren765LT #McLaren765LTSpider #Supercar #McLaren

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by McLaren Automotive on July 30, 2021. May be an image of car, road and text that says '1 LT05 MCL'.

node.text:
Like the 765LT Coupe, the Spider has an unmistakable LT front splitter, side skirts, and enlarged lower side air intakes – all dedicated to managing airflow and cooling. Combined with the lowered suspension and widened front track, the advanced aerodynamics deliver an intensity of driver engagement that has become a Longtail trademark. Once experienced, never forgotten. ​

#McLaren765LT #McLaren765LTSpider #Supercar #McLaren

Did you know, the new Longtail active rear wing is 20% larger than the 720S Spider’s. With a revised profile to maximise downforce in corners, and reduce stopping distances. Our incredible engineers also created the bespoke carbon fibre front floor, which increases front downforce and maintains it during high-speed braking.​

#McLaren765LT #McLaren765LTSpider #Supercar #McLaren

node.text:
The immense performance and dynamic prowess of the new McLaren 765LT Spider, are enhanced by three compelling factors: the strength of its MonoCage II-S structure, the game-changing design of its one-piece Retractable Hard Top roof, and the ongoing determination of McLaren engineers to pursue the company’s philosophy of super-lightweight engineering.​

#McLaren765LT #McLaren765LTSpider #Supercar #McLaren

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by McLaren Automotive on July 29, 2021. May be an image of car and road.

node.text:
Did you know, the 765LT Spider boasts, 0-60mph in 2.7 seconds, 0-100km/h (62mph) in 2.8 seconds and 0-200km/h (124mph) in 7.2 seconds.​

#McLaren765LT #McLaren765LTSpider #Supercar #McLaren ​

#McLaren765LT #McLaren765LTSpider #Supercar #McLaren ​
